sql:
SELECT neighborhood_name, average_property_price
FROM neighborhoods
WHERE average_property_price > (SELECT AVG(average_property_price) FROM neighborhoods);

SELECT n.neighborhood_name
FROM neighborhoods n
WHERE n.average_property_price > (
    SELECT AVG(average_property_price)
    FROM neighborhoods
);

external_knowledge:
- "old gold treasures" metaphorically refers to the properties;
- "hiding in the heart of Uptown" represents properties located in the 'Uptown' neighborhood;
- The average selling price is calculated for properties that have been sold, denoted by the 'sale' transaction type.
